The paper deals with a problem of constructing a training dataset from multiple private data sources while ensuring privacy and minimizing statistical distance from a target validation set. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given that the paper proposes a novel protocol for achieving differential privacy while ensuring quality guarantees, cs.LG and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also involves techniques from hashing, auctioning, and data summarization, which are relevant to cs.DS, cs.DB, and cs.AI.
